Liz Claiborne Plans Write-Off
Liz Claiborne also said that it expects to begin shipping
new goods to Macy now that an interim line of $60 million in
debtor-in-possession financing has been approved by U.S.
Bankruptcy Judge Burton Lifland.
   In late New York Stock Exchange trading yesterday, Liz
Claiborne shares rose 50 cents to $43.
   Separately, Macy said that it intends to go forward as
scheduled with its plans to open a new store in the Mall of
America in Minneapolis this August.